Well, I've tired to do what I can to get a copy-pastable example.

The program currently uses Pandas to query a PostgresSQL database. The results populate a DataFrame. To get you an example with real data, I exported the DataFrame into a dict using Pandas's to_dict function. I created a new DataFrame from the dict using the from_dict method.

I then used the groupby with one of the columns that was giving me the issues. And it work. It worked just as it should. I then tried it on the original DataFrame, populated from PostgreSQL, and it gives me the error I'm posting about. What gives with that?

I'm sorry, I'm not sure how to get you something that will re-produce the error now.
ok so where you get the error, show `df.info()`, and `df.head()` (before the groupby)
